Team E.L.I.T.E. is proud to present the CAD model for our 2024 robot, xtrēmachēn 27!

Note: Our team uses SOLIDWORKS, included is a Pack & Go, as well as a .step file of the main assembly. You can find an Onshape import, here.

0032058×1926 3.82 MB

This is our 27th season of Encouraging Learning In Technology and Engineering. We attended the Hudson Valley regional, and captained the #5 alliance with our partners 1155 and 250. At the end of the event we were awarded the Industrial Design Award.

Next, we attended the Buckeye Regional where we again captained the #5 alliance with our partners 4145 and 2603. After assisting a variety of teams on practice day get competition ready, our team was awarded with the Gracious Professionalism Award.

Lastly, we attended the Miami Valley Regional where, you guessed it, we captained the #5 alliance captain and played again with our friends 4145, 5740, and 4576. Ending our competition season with a 25-15-0 record.

You may have also seen our robot at a variety of offseason events including the Ohio State Championship, Battlecry, Shawshank Showdown, Curiosity Open, & CORI. We’d like to thank all of our alliance partners from this offseason for working with our team to achieve our highest potential.

Thank you to our off-season partners:

144, 695, 1787, 1991, 2603, 4150, 4546, 4601, 6153, 8140, and 9622.

Below you can find handouts which our students present and hand out to judges.

XM27_Page11440×1864 346 KB

XM27_Page21440×1864 299 KB

Additionally, we’ve worked on a few side projects this off-season to improve our design portfolio. Our primary focus this year was linear motion, which we are historically bad at, having not made an elevator since the 2018 season (which was not good).

Check out the various elevators and telescoping tube that we’ve made and let us know what you think!

Off-season Side Projects

Chain Driven Cascade Elevator

Continuous Elevator

Round Tube Continuous Elevator

Lead Screw Driven Telescoping Arm

Timing Belt Driven Continuous Elevator

Timing Belt Driven Cascade Elevator

For any questions about our 2024 robot, feel free to reach out to myself or @A_Reed in this thread, or though DM’s. Good luck in REEFSCAPE!
